<ul><li><a class="l" href="#pf1" data-dest-detail='[1,"XYZ",57,719,null]'>EC 2 &amp; 3 Modals - Can, Could &amp;         May</a><ul><li><a class="l" href="#pf1" data-dest-detail='[1,"XYZ",57,650,null]'>Can, could &amp; may are modal verbs. A modal verb is not the main verb. A modal verb &quot;modifies&quot; or adds meaning to a main verb.</a></li><li><a class="l" href="#pf1" data-dest-detail='[1,"XYZ",57,427,null]'>*Use the subject &quot;I&quot; with may.  Don&apos;t use the subject you.</a></li></ul></li><li><a class="l" href="#pf2" data-dest-detail='[2,"XYZ",64,440,null]'>Grammar Form - Not Giving Permission</a></li><li><a class="l" href="#pf2" data-dest-detail='[2,"XYZ",64,408,null]'>Can&apos;t &amp; May Not</a><ul><li><a class="l" href="#pf2" data-dest-detail='[2,"XYZ",64,225,null]'>Use the base form of a verb after a modal.</a></li></ul></li></ul>